{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase income tax allowance for necessary living costs for basic rate payers",
        "additional_details": "With the cost of living crisis, I'm calling on the Government to allow ordinary basic rate tax payers to do the same!\r\n \r\nBusinesses raking in millions, if not billions, in profits are allowed to offset their expenditure (rent, rates, employee pay etc.) against their profits before they have to pay tax on the remainder.\r\n \r\nThe ordinary person doesn't have this luxury and all of their above their personal tax-free allowance is taxed.\r\n \r\nAllowing specific 'necessary' outgoings to be tax exempt could help to boost the economy by giving people more disposable income to spend!\r\n",
        "background": "Businesses of all shapes, sizes and incomes are permitted to offset their expenditure against their profits, and only the money left over is taxed.",
